Company Description

About SEEK

SEEK’s portfolio of diverse businesses make a positive impact on a truly global scale. Our purpose is to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives and help organisations succeed. We create world-class technology solutions to connect more people to relevant employment, education, small business and volunteer opportunities. We have a culture of high-performance in our workplaces and celebrate the diversity of our employees who contribute to the success of our organisation.

Life at SEEK

SEEK’s purpose is at the centre of everything we do. Our SEEK, which defines the way we work, is all about what makes us unique and a little bit different. Passion, Team, Delivery and Future are our principles that drive innovation and creativity. SEEK strives to support employee wellbeing by providing an amazing experience at work which led us to being named AFR BOSS Top 10 Best Places to Work in Technology (2021-2024). We are proud to work in an environment that's inclusive where everyone's unique ideas, experiences and perspectives are valued.

Our award-winning head office in Cremorne (just a 4 min walk from Richmond station) provides an exceptional space to collaborate with colleagues. The building provides sweeping views of the city, a games area, sit and stand desks at every workstation, modern end-of-trip facilities and Thursday night drinks which gives our people an opportunity to connect in a social setting.

Job Description

Why This Role?

At SEEK, we believe infrastructure is a strategic differentiator. In this Principal Architect role, you'll drive our enterprise-wide cloud, infrastructure and networking direction—ensuring our platforms are scalable, secure, and resilient to support AI, product velocity and operational excellence.

You’ll lead SEEK’s strategic thinking in poly-cloud architecture, high-performance compute, resilient connectivity, observability, cost optimisation, and network security—partnering with Engineering, Security, Architecture and Platform teams to uplift foundational capabilities. If you're excited by large-scale challenges, federated influence, and setting the direction for modern platform engineering—this is your opportunity.

What You’ll Be Doing

You’ll be the enterprise-wide lead for Cloud, Infrastructure & Network Architecture, and:

Define and evolve SEEK’s cloud, infra & network strategy, patterns and guardrails

Champion cloud-native platforms, poly-cloud approaches, and internal developer platforms

Simplify and consolidate architecture to improve cost, resilience and scale

Lead a small team of Solution Architects and mentor senior engineers across APAC

Partner with Security to embed zero-trust principles and compliance at scale

Collaborate with Product & Data teams to ensure infra supports AI, ML and emerging workloads

Provide architectural assurance and governance for SEEK’s most critical infra initiatives

Maintain clear blueprints, roadmaps and strategy artefacts to guide future uplift

Enable CI/CD, observability and traffic management foundations at a global scale

The Opportunity

You’ll sit within SEEK’s Platform Architecture team—partnering across Security, Data & AI, Enterprise and Customer domains. The work you lead will enable speed and resilience for thousands of systems and millions of users across APAC.

This is a career-defining opportunity to shape foundational capabilities and architectural practice in one of the region’s most dynamic product environments.

Qualifications

What We’re Looking For

Extensive experience in cloud, infrastructure and networking architecture

Strong technical breadth across compute, storage, network, observability & CI/CD

Deep expertise in poly-cloud, Kubernetes, service mesh, and cloud-native architecture

Demonstrated leadership in large-scale, federated environments

Strength in strategy translation—shaping roadmaps, guardrails and governance

Confident stakeholder engagement, mentoring and influencing across senior levels

Experience uplifting cost, security, developer experience and performance in parallel

Bonus: Experience supporting AI/ML infrastructure and advanced network design

Additional Information

At SEEK we offer:

Support of flexible working, including a mix of office and work from home days depending on your role.
Support for parents with 14 weeks paid primary carers leave and 2 weeks paid leave for partners
SEEK is committed to operating sustainably and is preparing for the impacts of climate change and the transition to a low-carbon future, and is working to minimise its environmental impacts which includes a long-term emissions reduction target of net zero by FY2050
The opportunity to work from anywhere for up to 4 weeks per financial year
Free income protection insurance

At SEEK, we are passionate about fostering a culture of inclusion and wellbeing that embraces and values the diversity of our people. We are a purpose driven business that works with heart.

We know teams with diverse ideas, experiences and perspectives are more creative and are critical to ensuring effective delivery and innovating to enable our future success. As such, we welcome applications from people with diverse backgrounds and life experiences, especially as they relate to gender, sexual identity, culture, faith, disability and life stages. If you have the skills, curiosity and an adaptable mindset but don't meet every responsibility or qualification listed in this advertisement, please still get in touch with us.

Should you require any specific support or adjustments throughout the recruitment process and beyond, please advise us and we will be happy to assist.

For this role, only those candidates with the eligible right to work will be considered.

SEEK kindly requests no unsolicited resumes or approaches from recruitment agencies and will not be responsible for any associated fees.

MND Australia is the national peak body of state organisations that support those living with and impacted by motor neurone disease (MND). Since 1993, we have been the voice for the MND community. We work collaboratively with our member organisations, the state MND Associations, to inform, influence and raise awareness and understanding of Motor Neurone Disease (MND) at a national level through advancing research, advocacy and high-quality care for patients and carers to self-manage the disease, supported by specialist input.

About the Role

This position will support the more effective use of data and technology across the MND Australia’s activities including growing registrations and the use of the MiNDAUS Registry; support the Data, Innovation and Technology Committee; support the research funding program; and improvements in MND Australia’s operational activities. The position will work with MND Australia’s CEO and staff, the Data, Innovation and Technology Committee, State Associations and other stakeholders.

 

Key responsibilities

1.       Manage the development of the MiNDAUS Registry including growing patient and clinical users, enhancement of functionality and improving the use of Registry data 

2.       Support increasing MND Australia’s advocacy, care and research activities through better use of data, technology and evidence

3.       Advice and implementation support on the best use of technology within MND Australia

4.       Consideration and advice on emerging technology use, ethical considerations and implications such as AI, machine learning, and data analytics

5.       Advice and support to the Data, Innovation and Technology Committee.

 

About You

1.       Experience and qualifications in data analytics and data use

2.       Proven project management skills

3.       Experience in working in the health sector, preferably with MND or neurological conditions

4.       A ‘can do’ attitude and pragmatic approach to work

5.       Proven interpersonal skills including the ability to work with diverse stakeholders and people with disabilities

Position Type

This is a fulltime contract position to 30 June 2027 (with possibility for extension), ideally based in Canberra, reporting to the Chief Executive Officer.

Benefits

We provide various benefits including:

·         Friendly and supportive team

·         Flexible work arrangements to best balance work priorities and your family, study and other personal commitments

·         MND Australia is a Health Promotion Charity and can offer FBT exemption in salary packaging

About Rubidium Light & the RB Rover

Rubidium develops automation and inspection solutions for the sports and lighting industries. Our flagship product, the RB Rover, is a field robot that performs sports lighting audits — driving measurement grids across sports fields to collect illumination and positional data for compliance, reporting and design feedback.

We are now entering the next phase of RB Rover’s development: redesigning its body for durability and manufacturability, and upgrading its Cube-based navigation and control system for robust, repeatable, autonomous operation.

The Role

We’re looking for a Robotics Product Engineer (Mechanical & Controls) to take ownership of the redesign and system upgrades. You’ll work hands-on across mechanical design, control system integration, and field testing, delivering a production-ready robot that can reliably complete missions in real-world sports-field conditions.

Key responsibilities

Redesign RB Rover’s chassis and sensor mast(s) with a focus on durability, weather resistance, weight distribution, and serviceability.

Engineer mounting and wiring solutions for payloads (lux meters, LiDAR, GNSS, cameras, IMU, encoders).

Design for manufacture — materials selection, processes, and production drawings.

Implement and tune navigation/control systems leveraging the Cube autopilot system (CubePilot/ArduPilot ecosystem).

Integrate and calibrate sensors into the Cube stack; develop robust sensor-fusion pipelines (GNSS, LiDAR, IMU, encoders).

Improve motion control, safety limits, and power management (battery systems, BMS integration, swap procedures).

Plan and conduct field testing, collecting telemetry and iterating designs.

Deliver complete engineering documentation (CAD, BOM, wiring diagrams, parameter sets, software/firmware notes, test reports, and maintenance guides).

About you

Must have:

Degree in Mechanical, Mechatronics, Robotics Engineering, or equivalent.

3–7+ years experience designing outdoor/industrial products.

Hands-on robotics/control system experience with CubePilot/ArduPilot or PX4.

Strong skills in CAD (SolidWorks, Fusion360, or similar).

Embedded systems experience: Cube autopilot integration, motor controllers, companion computers.

Field testing and iteration experience.

Nice to have:

Experience with RTK GNSS, LiDAR-based SLAM/localization.

Designing to IP ratings (IP54–IP65).

Industrial design or ergonomics experience.

Prior experience with outdoor inspection/agricultural robots.

Knowledge of DFMA and supplier engagement in Australia/APAC.

Tools & platforms you’ll use

Cube autopilot (CubePilot/ArduPilot, MAVLink)

ROS/ROS2 for higher-level logic

CAD: SolidWorks / Fusion360

LiDAR, GNSS, IMU, cameras

Embedded platforms: Cube + companion computer (Jetson/Raspberry Pi)

What success looks like

Robust Cube-based navigation stack that completes ≥95% of missions without manual rescue.

Positional repeatability of <0.2 m across audit grids.

Serviceable, weather-resistant body design ready for production.

Comprehensive documentation for manufacturing and operation.

Why join us?

Be part of a pioneering robotics product in the sports technology sector.

Hands-on role with direct impact from design through to field deployment.

Flexible work pattern, based in Queensland with real-world testing on sports fields.

Contract or permanent pathway available.

How to apply

If you’re passionate about robotics, control systems, and designing for the real world, we’d love to hear from you.


Apply via Seek with your CV and portfolio, highlighting relevant projects in mechanical design and Cube/ArduPilot integration.

Rubidium Light — Advancing sports and lighting technology with robotics innovation.

Principal Data Engineer – Contract ($1125 All In Per Day)

One of Australia’s leading tech organisations is seeking a Principal Data Engineer for an initial 3-month contract.

This role demands a hands-on expert who can quickly solve complex problems and optimise large-scale data processing systems across both batch and streaming workloads.

The focus of the engagement is performance and cost optimisation in AWS, with responsibility for reducing latency and managing cloud spend effectively. You’ll lead the end-to-end design and delivery of scalable data solutions, from understanding source systems through to actionable insights.

Beyond technical delivery, you’ll drive efficiency across distributed systems, enhance data quality with new sources and rules, and support advanced analytics such as anomaly detection and forecasting. As a Principal, you’ll set technical standards, mentor peers, and embed best practice in Agile, TDD, and CI/CD, while collaborating across teams in a fast-paced environment.

Key Skills

Data Engineering at Scale: Proven expertise with AWS (S3, Kinesis, Glue, CloudFormation, SNS) in distributed environments.
Pipelines & Processing: Advanced experience with Airflow, DBT, Spark, Flink, Hive, Kafka, and Databricks.
Programming & Modelling: Strong Python and SQL; design and optimise extensible data models for performance.
ML & Analytics: Skilled in embedding machine learning into production systems, incl. forecasting and anomaly detection.
Leadership & Practices: Experienced in mentoring, code reviews, and applying Agile, TDD, and CI/CD to data engineering.
The team has high standards in their data engineering practises, so looking to connect with the best in market, a real opportunity to add a significant brand to your portfolio.

Send your up to date CV to bendavies@preacta.com and let's book some time in.

Solentive is an Australian-owned Digital Technology Consultancy, dedicated to helping businesses succeed by providing them with Software Automation & AI products and services. With over 30 years of experience, we help businesses achieve meaningful digital transformation by delivering the right technology solutions tailored to their needs. 

Our culture is built on collaboration, curiosity, and a drive for excellence. We work as a team to solve complex challenges, learn from each other, and push the boundaries of what’s possible with technology. 

We are seeking an experienced Technical Consultant to join our team and play a pivotal role in shaping the future of our clients' success through AI, automation, and digital transformation. This role gives you the opportunity to tackle complex challenges, work on a variety of projects, and help businesses unlock their full potential with AI-powered, innovative technology solutions. You’ll also have the chance to contribute to and maintain Solentive’s long standing reputation as a technology leader through delivery. 

If you thrive on solving problems, collaborating with forward-thinking minds, and welcome a challenge, this role is for you. We’re looking for someone who communicates with confidence and enjoys working with both people and technology to create meaningful, lasting improvements in the way businesses operate. 

Key Responsibilities:    

Facilitate technical discovery workshops with clients and prospects to help them identify and understand their technical requirements, including AI needs.  

Implementation, support, and management of products including InRule and the Microsoft Stack, with a focus on AI integration. 

Effectively set expectations with clients and manage communication and deliverables associated with the provision of consulting services. 

Provide product training to clients.  

Create and manage documentation.  

Determine fit-for-purpose solutions to clients that consider technical, functional, and commercial objectives, with a focus on AI-driven innovations. 

Provide product demonstrations to prospective clients. 

Provide accurate cost estimates for the implementation of products and services. 

Build trusted relationships with clients through technical thought leadership and expert advice. 

Excite prospective clients by communicating ideas, opportunities, and potential solutions, particularly in the realm of AI and automation. 

Identify upsell opportunities by recommending Solentive’s products and services to existing clients. 

Essential Skills:  

You have a growth mindset and a passion for continuous learning in the tech space, especially in AI. 

You excel at understanding & analysing client technology requirements and recommending fit-for-purpose solutions. 

You hold creative and pragmatic problem-solving skills to design innovative solutions across industries and budgets. 

You have a strong ability to estimate tasks accurately and deliver within scope, timeframes, and budgets. 

You are an excellent communicator with both clients and technical team members at all levels. 

You are detail-oriented and self-managed, ensuring client expectations are met with quality outcomes. 

You are passionate about delivering results and driving excellence in every aspect of your work. 

You are a self-motivated team player who brings energy, enthusiasm, and innovative thinking to client engagements. 

You thrive in producing high-quality documentation for various audiences. 

You play a key role in advancing the Consulting group, driving outstanding results. 

You have 5+ years of technical Consulting & Product Implementation consulting experience. 

You have experience implementing solutions on Microsoft 365 and Azure tech stack including Power Platform, Dynamics 365, Fabric, API Management, Function Apps, Logic Apps, Graph API. 

You hold or are willing to obtain Microsoft Certifications in Power Platform, Azure AI & Data, and Dynamics 365. 

Why choose us?  At Solentive, we value our people and have created an environment where you can do your best work. Here’s what’s on offer: 

A supportive and inclusive work environment that encourages professional growth and development.  

Opportunities to work on exciting and innovative projects with a diverse range of clients across all industries.  

Opportunities to experience a variety of software technologies in different domains, with a strong emphasis on AI. 

A commitment to work-life balance, employee well-being, and fantastic benefits including:

Hybrid working and flexible hours

Additional loyalty leave -1 & 2-weeks additional leave annually at relevant tenure milestones

Team lunches & activities

Health & fitness benefits

Experience in the following areas is highly desirable but not essential:  

Experience in data engineering and data migrations (skills such as SQL and NoSQL databases, Azure Data Factory, Azure Synapse, Power BI.) 

Software engineering (skills such as Agile, CI/CD and Git-based repos, .NET 5.0+ and C# 9.0+, SQL and NoSQL Storage, RESTful APIs.) 

Certifications in Generative AI and Machine Learning (Coursera, Deeplearning.ai)  

Experience in implementing Business Rule Management (BRE) platforms.  

If you are ready to take your career to the next level and make a meaningful impact, we invite you to apply for the Technical Consultant position at Solentive.

How to apply:   

Apply via Seek or through the Solentive website - https://www.solentive.com/careers or contact us directly by email to jobs@solentive.com

Senior Data Engineer

$200k – $230k package · Sydney or Remote (Australia)

About the Company

Join a fast-growing technology business that builds modern data and analytics platforms to power customer and market insights.
They value trust, collaboration and autonomy, with a culture that rewards impact and supports life outside of work.

About the Role

As Senior Data Engineer, you’ll design and operate the core data environment that ingests, organises and serves high-volume customer and market data.
This is a hands-on position blending data engineering and data infrastructure, focusing on R, Python and SQL and working across on-premises and cloud environments.

What You’ll Do

Design and build scalable, high-performance data pipelines to ingest and process large, complex datasets from multiple internal and external sources.

Model and manage data flows and schemas to ensure quality, consistency and reliability.

Implement best practices in data governance, access control, monitoring and observability.

Work with product and analytics teams to align data architecture with business goals.

Automate infrastructure provisioning and deployments using modern DevOps and Infrastructure-as-Code tools.

Provide production support, including continuous improvement of system performance, availability and disaster recovery.

What You Bring

Degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics or equivalent experience.

Proficiency in R, Python and SQL with strong data modelling and query optimisation skills.

Solid understanding of distributed systems, modern data storage (e.g. S3, columnar stores) and streaming technologies (e.g. Kafka).

Experience with cloud platforms (AWS, GCP) and Linux.

Familiarity with orchestration tools (Airflow, Dagster) and container technologies (Docker, Kubernetes).

Strong communication skills and the ability to work effectively in small, fast-moving teams as well as larger enterprise environments.

Nice to Have

Experience working end-to-end in small, agile environments, taking full ownership of design and delivery.

Exposure to modern data formats (Delta Lake, Apache Iceberg) and data lakehouse architectures.

Experience with observability tools (Prometheus, Grafana).

Why Join

Play a key role in shaping a greenfield data platform used for advanced analytics and data-driven decision making.

Work with modern tooling across both cloud and on-prem environments.

Join a supportive, collaborative culture with flexibility for remote work.

Software Engineer – Manufacturing Management Systems

With over 1,000 employees worldwide, we partner with clients to deliver scalable software solutions across industries including manufacturing, retail, finance, healthcare, and government. Our culture is built on trust, transparency, and long-term relationships—helping businesses succeed while fostering a meaningful workplace for our people.

About the Role

This is a full-time hybrid role for a Software Engineer - Manufacturing Management System located in Greater Melbourne Area, with some work-from-home flexibility. The Software Engineer will be responsible for developing, testing, and maintaining software systems for manufacturing management. Day-to-day tasks include coding, debugging, and optimizing software solutions, collaborating with cross-functional teams to understand and implement requirements, and ensuring the effective performance of the manufacturing management system.

Key Responsibilities

Develop, test, and optimize MMS features, tools, and processes.

Build and maintain web applications using .NET and ColdFusion.

Write clean, scalable, and maintainable code.

Troubleshoot and resolve software issues promptly.

Participate in requirements gathering, design, development, testing, and deployment.

Analyze user/business needs and implement system enhancements.

Stay current with industry technologies and best practices.

Support ERP (JDE/others) integration and web services.

Skills & Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, IT, or related field.

Minimum 3+ years of ColdFusion experience.

Strong UI development skills: jQuery, Bootstrap, HTML, CSS, JavaScript.

Proficiency in:

.NET, RESTful APIs, Git, Azure DevOps

Ad Text:
About ACMI

ACMI is your museum of screen culture. Watch, play, make and discover the universe of screen-based art, films, TV and videogames. Visit us in Naarm/Melbourne's Fed Square, online and on tour. Our museum attracts millions of visitors through a vibrant offer of exhibitions, screenings, commissions and festivals. ACMI's industry, education and creative incubator programs inspire and develop the next generation of screen creatives. We are a globally recognised hub that connects people, communities, technology and ideas to shape our futures. More at acmi.net.au

About the role

ACMI is seeking a Platform Reliability Engineer to manage reliability, security, and scalability of the ACMI's ICT infrastructure across on-premise and cloud environments. The role plays a critical part in maintaining high availability of services, implementing robust disaster recovery strategies, and proactively identifying and resolving system issues. This is a new full-time ongoing role reporting to the Head of Systems & Infrastructure.

What you'll bring to the role

Relevant qualifications and practical experience working with: Cisco networking products and protocols, cloud services Azure and AWS supporting networking and compute and Logic Monitor or similar. Strong working knowledge of LANs, SANs, Azure, AWS, VMware, ICT security systems, wireless networks, firewalls, routers, core switches, and server/network monitoring tools.
Extensive hands-on experience managing ICT infrastructure across on-premises and cloud environments, with strong technical expertise in Windows, Linux, and macOS systems.
Strong knowledge of network and system security practices, including experience with anti-virus, spam prevention, and endpoint protection tools.
Experience designing and implementing disaster recovery and business continuity strategies.
Highly developed conceptual and analytical skills applicable to successful technical troubleshooting, problem solving across a range of technical/ systems applications/issues and ability to evaluate and implement continual improvements to ICT support systems.

What we offer

Full-time ongoing Grade 4.1 role, with a starting salary of $97,955 plus super.
A talented, committed and creative team of people with a passion for screen culture, technology and media, cultural diversity, and inspiring new forms of creativity in our communities. A museum and workspace that provides an exceptional space to collaborate with colleagues located in the heart of Melbourne in Federation Square (just a 5 min walk from Flinders Street station).
As a valued team member, you can enjoy complimentary and discounted tickets, discounts at our shop and cafe, access to wellbeing activities, learning and development programs and our Employee Assistance Program. Flexible working, including a mix of onsite and work from home days depending on your role. Visit the ACMI website to learn more about working with us.

How to apply

To obtain a position description and apply online visit ACMI Careers. Follow the online application process, submit your resume and a one-page cover letter explaining why you're interested in the role and how your experience makes you a good fit. Please contact us via peopleandculture@acmi.net.au or 03 8663 2200 to discuss making adjustments to the recruitment process for your accessibility needs.

Applications close Sunday 5 October 2025 at 11:59pm.

Please note interviews will be held on Tuesday 14 October 2025.

ACMI is a child safe workplace and actively promotes the safety, wellbeing and inclusion of all children from all backgrounds. ACMI is an equal opportunity employer, committed to building an inclusive workplace that supports diverse thinking and innovation. We encourage applications from First Nations People, people of culturally diverse backgrounds, Deaf and Disabled people and people from the LGBTIQA+ community. All sectors of the community are welcome to apply.

Applicants must be an Australian Citizen, Permanent Resident or hold a valid work permit or visa. Work eligibility will be checked as part of the recruitment process. The successful applicant is required to complete reference and background checks prior to employment, including a Working with Children Check where required and National Police Check.

Daily AI coding tool user (Claude Code, Cursor, Copilot)

Exceptional async communication

Built platforms that scale (not just apps)

History of 10x productivity gains using AI tools

Ship fast, learn faster: These tools are evolving weekly - we build, test, iterate

Own your decisions: No committees - you architect it, you build it, you own it

Who You'll Work With

Our exceptional team and you'll work directly with the founder, a proven entrepreneur who's built and exited companies before. No layers, no politics - direct access to leadership and immediate impact on company direction. This isn't his first rodeo, and he knows how to build both products and teams.

The Package

Growth:

Direct path to senior positions in this expanding role

10-20% time for R&D/experimentation with new AI tools

All cloud and AI certifications covered

Daily collaboration with proven technical leadership

Cutting edge: Using tools that most developers haven't heard of yet
